
<p>Large enterprises?<br>Small businesses?<br>Threat actors watch them.</p>



<p>They want your data.<br>They hunt for your money.</p>



<p>Whales defend themselves.<br>Dedicated security teams.<br>Budget for tools.</p>



<p>Small businesses?<br>Vulnerable.<br>No security team.<br>No IT budget.<br>No shield.<br>Easy targets.</p>



<p>For you, protection comes in a different form.</p>



<span id="more-7950"></span>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="org0fde401">Open-source Software &#8211; The Ghost&#8217;s Toolset</h3>



<p>Open-source is auditable.<br>Read the code.<br>Understand it.</p>



<p>You&#8217;re not tied to vendors.<br>Low costs or even free.</p>



<p>Used it? Buy the devs a coffee.<br>Respect the Operator who deploys it.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="orgf734c11">Linux Is The Firewall</h3>



<p>UFW is light.<br>Iptables is a silent blade.<br>Dedicated firewall distros for perimeter defenses.</p>



<p>You don&#8217;t need the price of a space ship.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="orgdb98673">Password Vaults Of Ghost Ops</h3>



<p>Use Passbolt for small teams.<br>Vaultwarden fits lightweight orgs.<br>KeepassXC is the vault of client side.</p>



<p>Both used by Ghosts.<br>Trusted.<br>Audited.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="orgc5fc042">Silent Office Toolset</h3>



<p>LibreOffice is freedom.<br>But plain text is not a shame.<br>Emacs Org-Mode is advanced.<br>Markdown is simple and effective.</p>



<p>No telemetry, no noise.<br>No subscriptions, no hidden costs.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="orgef56dd4">Secure Mail</h3>



<p>Proton Mail is encrypted.<br>Easy to use. Ghost grade privacy.<br>Self-hosted mail? Hard. But possible.<br>Use GnuPG for additional encryption.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="org3785604">Secure Communications</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Element (Matrix)</li>



<li>SimpleX Chat</li>
</ul>



<p>Use end to end encrypted comms.<br>Host your own servers.</p>



<p>Avoid WhatsApp. Avoid compromise.</p>



